750x930/1cdc3cac-7cd6-44dd-b6d2-9cfff1eee506--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.12.26_PM.png 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n          \u003cspan\u003eLayers of the date caramel bars.\u003c/span\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Anna Arriaga\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003cp\u003eThe first of the three layers is the almond flour base. I mixed 1 1/4 cup of almond flour, 3 teaspoons of maple syrup, and 3 teaspoons of melted coconut oil (any neutral oil is fine). I mixed that with a spatula until fully combined and then spread it out in a 9x9 pan until flat and smooth. This crust baked for 12 minutes in a 350 Fahrenheit degree oven. It’s imperative that you give this base ample time to cool before assembling the other layers, or else it wont set.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-description=\"The date caramel ingredients before blending.\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageInteraction\" data-ga-event-action=\"Pinterest Share\" data-ga-event-label=\"Article Body Image\" data-ga-destination-url=\"none\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 16.9 20.8\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16.8 6.3C16.5 3.2 13.6.4 10.1.1 4.8-.5.1 2.7 0 7.9c0 2.4.8 4 2.9 4.8 1.5-1.5-.3-2.4-.5-4C2 4.3 7.1.1 11.7 2.9c3.2 1.9 2.6 9.9-1.2 10.7-.8.1-1.8-.1-2.1-.5-1.9-1.8 1.5-4.8.4-7.3-.9-2.1-3.6-.4-3.9 1.5-.2 1 .3 2 .3 2.9 0 2.1-1.3 5-1.7 7.1-.2.9-.3 2.6-.1 3.4h1.5c1-1.6 1.6-4.1 2.1-6.3.3-.2.5.4.7.6 1.8 1.4 5 .6 6.4-.7 2.1-1.7 3-5.2 2.7-8\" fill=\"currentColor\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n      \u003c/a\u003e\n\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAA