com/Xnp-4ody7lZ5DmDgDPltKVDu7Xo=/750x854/filters:format(webp)/3f784e5c-6964-46dc-a6e3-4d027ec8c960--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.10.58_PM.png 2x\"/\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/Vsiy-mvR9Mlm4uqqOa_4brfj324=/375x427/3f784e5c-6964-46dc-a6e3-4d027ec8c960--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.10.58_PM.png, https://images.food52.com/VC0nRnPaOtqk7rR-Dj4cjdfWCWs=/750x854/3f784e5c-6964-46dc-a6e3-4d027ec8c960--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.10.58_PM.png 2x\" alt=\"The date caramel ingredients before blending.\" width=\"964\" height=\"1099\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/Vsiy-mvR9Mlm4uqqOa_4brfj324=/375x427/3f784e5c-6964-46dc-a6e3-4d027ec8c960--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.10.58_PM.png, https://images.food52.com/VC0nRnPaOtqk7rR-Dj4cjdfWCWs=/750x854/3f784e5c-6964-46dc-a6e3-4d027ec8c960--Screenshot_2025-03-03_at_5.10.58_PM.png 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n          \u003cspan\u003eThe date caramel ingredients before blending.\u003c/span\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Anna Arriaga\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003cp\u003eThe second layer is the date caramel mixture. I chose to soak my dates in hot water before blending them to make sure the caramel came out a bit smoother, but it’s optional. I added 12 soaked dates, about ⅓ cup of peanut butter (any nut butter works), 1 tablespoon of melted coconut oil, and a teaspoon of vanilla extract to a food processor and pulsed until smooth. Honestly, I could eat this date caramel straight up, but I had to trust the process for the sake of these heavenly dessert bars.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-description=\"The almond base and date caramel.\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageIntera